bio: Annie and the Bang Bang are a four-piece rock band from Minneapolis. Inspired by music they heard as kids in the seventies and by the songs they put on mixtapes in the nineties, they're a little Fleetwood Mac meets Nirvana or Heart meets R.E.M. A classic sound from a parallel universe, they make little drive-in movies you can dance to.

porch_address: 2601 Hennepin Ave S - Sencha Tea Bar
bio: Atomic Lights are a 3 piece punk band from Minneapolis.  They started in the summer of 2012 and have been melting faces ever since.

Known for taking songs that you know and love and playing them in a way you've never heard them before, B+ Brass brings an incredibly high-powered brass band sound. Featuring sizzling sax solos, screaming trumpet lines, powerhouse low brass, and smashing drums, B+ Brass has something for everyone! You'll find that they are much more than just slightly above average. ;)
Angy / Sad songs that don't sound too angry or sad.
Veteran singer songwriters unite for trio project

Brand new 3-piece powerhouse Cheap Bouquet has hit the ground running in Minneapolis and aren't looking back. The trio is carving out a new path in the pop punk scene, through unapologetic authenticity and drawing influence from icons across the rock and alternative spectrum. Fronted by long time listener, first time frontman Sam Awad, with Twin City scene vets Chelsea Oxborough and Brandon Evilla on guitars, Cheap Bouquet is the amalgamation of a broad range of individual experience. The band has found their footing with a dynamic sound, candid storytelling, and, more than anything else, a genuine joy to be sharing their music.

Crush Scene is a four piece Minneapolis based ya’llternative rock band feat members of The Toxenes, Cicada Collective and Mad Mojo Jett that writes cheeky songs which emphasize the importance of keeping a safe scene for everyone to have crushes in.

Damn Phibian are a four-piece eclectic indie rock band from Minneapolis, MN. The band formed in 2023 from a collection of nerdy, cat-loving MPLS transplants who bonded over their love of Radiohead, Ween, and Wilco. They fuse diverse guitar tones and a groovy rhythm section to keep the crowd dancing to catchy riffs and weird time signatures all night long. They’re not sure if the terrible puns between songs help or hinder their live performances, but that’s not gonna stop them from telling them!

Rancho Unicorno formed after college friends Felice and Kareem combined their musical tastes and talents to curate a set of acoustic tunes that'll have y'all dancing and singing to a new generation of classics. Come join us for a celebration of music, humans, and unicorns!

band_name: Dee Langley and the Masked Accordions
bio: The Masked Accordions is a masked, mass accordion band led by Dee Langley, a longtime professional accordionist who has performed with the Minnesota Orchestra and the St. Paul Chamber Orchestra. Langley is a member of the American Accordion Hall of Fame, a recipient of the McKnight Fellowship for Performing Musicians and is the founder of the NE Accordion Festival.
Musical project based around the sweetest, closest harmonies we can muster.

drey dk is a songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, & producer based in Minneapolis, MN. They debuted their first single back in September of 2019, with a couple more singles and two EP’s to follow (as recent as May of 2022). Through minimalism, melodic/harmonic chord building, instrumental looping/layering and soundscapes, drey dk is able to pull you into their sonic yet emotive realm they create. Drawing inspiration from artists like Cocteau Twins, Beach House, and Caroline Polachek.

Emily Boyajian is a pianist and classical music composer, who uses her strong background in music theory to write music that is intellectually stimulating and emotionally captivating. She has written solo piano works, chamber music, orchestral music, and art songs. Outside of music, she also enjoys doing improv theater, playing board games, biking, and volunteering for LGBT groups.

Meet Fever Field, the cosmic gumbo of indie rock and pop hailing from Uptown, Minnesota. Formed in 2022 by St. John’s University friends, Jack Cassidy and Drew Lodermeier, this dynamic quartet creates a mesmerizing fusion of genres. Their music, a mix of original compositions and innovative covers, resonates with the vibrant culture of Uptown. Don't miss out on experiencing Fever Field's cosmic gumbo of melodies and energetic performances that truly stand out in the indie music scene.

band_name: Graydon Francis and The Tribe (Tarli x Midievil x IAMKAYE x Diatonic)
bio: Graydon Francis is a Liberian American singer/songwriter based in the Twin Cities, known for his Luther Vandross-like voice. After joining the Grammy-winning "Sounds of Blackness" in 2016, he enhanced his artistic skills under Gary Hines' direction and later performed with RuPaul's Drag Race winner Bebe Zahara Benet. Pursuing a solo career in 2017, Graydon collaborated with Liberian American artist Tarli on the album "Liberation" and the acclaimed music video "Come On." He has performed at festivals like Melhaven Music Festival and Jackson Indie Music Week and headlined events, including Minneapolis' "Concert at the Commons" and Icehouse. As a background vocalist, he features in "The Music of Gladys Knight and the Pips" across the Twin Cities. Graydon is redefining his sound with the afrobeat-inspired single "Ginger," released October 6, 2023.

On a mission to help others through music during these absurd times with her compassionate and thoughtful approach, Hawthorne Oachs writes about issues that affect teens (and many adults) in staggering numbers. Hawthorne releases these songs in hopes that it will create more awareness and spark healthy conversation around mental health, while ultimately helping others feel less alone. 

Through her music, Hawthorne offers a community where mental health, psychological safety, and connection are at the forefront, and she does this by channeling her empathy and compassion. She creates a sense of belonging, mattering, and a safe place for anyone who feels out of space and time, lost in the darkness, or frustrated by the uncertainty, and she does it all while defying the notion that "kids should be seen and not heard." 

Hawthorne Oachs is a teen multi-hyphenate musical artist, digital artist, and award-nominated actress who has spent the last three years of her life writing, producing, and releasing songs while also balancing being a full-time student, playing her first festivals, comic book stores, coffee shops, acting in a few projects, and creating the cover art for her songs.
Hella Reptilian, Dingus, KV$KET, Willows, and Yare

Honey Please is an indie pop rock band out of Minneapolis Minnesota. Through a shared joy of musical expression and a love of performing, they have delighted many ears around the Twin Cities area. The band formed in the fall of 2022 and have been creating new tunes since. All original songs are written by singer-guitarist Sam Scheuneman who has been writing songs since he learned to speak. Bassist Dawson Ludvigson adds intricate bass melodies under a light melody sung by Sam. Guitarist Jack Nobel shreds lead lines to give each song its unique timbre. On the drums, Joe Kiser continues to keep beats fresh and alive with a lively and energetic tone. Together these musicians create a sound that feels complete and is full of emotion. When playing live the audience just cannot stop dancing and moving along to the beat. Honey Please has released two singles "Losing Composure/Flute" in December '23 and are currently working on their first studio album set to release August '24.

HUNNY BEAR is a funk/fusion quartet located in Minneapolis, MN. Featuring a combination of styles and performing music ranging from modern covers, funk standards, fresh sounds and originals, everyone is sure to enjoy the cool vibes and energy at any performance.

Mommy Log Balls was formed in the early 90s by members of Duck Kicking Vulture, Yanomamos, and Likehell and continues the tradition of the proto-punk roots of garage rock and avant-garde noise and performance art.

MY COUSIN DALLAS was born in a Wisconsin college radio station, took their first steps out of a coffeehouse series to spend the next two decades giving the Midwest a good answer to the question, 'What exactly is Cowpunk?'
Best described as "The Replacements and The Barenaked Ladies getting together and covering Duran Duran, a performance by My Cousin Dallas is an eclectic adventure.

6 - 9 piece Minneapolis based indie/rock band with a brass and string section delivering eclectic sounds, unique lyrics and a powerful message. Our mission is to use our music to fight against racism and inequity.

porch_address: 2601 Hennepin Ave S - Sencha Tea Bar
bio: Night Jobs formed in 2017 between two friends. A Texan and a Nebraskan colliding in Minneapolis, MN with a shared love of the rock n’ roll sounds emanating from basements and dives of the upper-Midwest. The idea was to keep things simple and wear their influences proudly on their sleeves. An emotionally tinged punk rock trio yelling out sing alongs hoping to make light of the bummers that life throws our way.

Oceanographer is a four piece multi genre band made up of LGBTQ folk. We make indie dream pop with country/folk and funk influence that focuses on the queer experience. We have a lot of pining sapphic love songs, and a lot of songs that are just plain silly. We love reverb and chorus!

Perf is constantly testing alternative styles and just released his second album earlier this year in March. He is a Twin Cities native and currently makes emo hip hop and sad rap with a plan to dive more into hyperpop. Current musical influences are 6 dogs, Yung Lean, Lil Peep, 93feetofsmoke, fish narc, and cr1tter.

Pity Party is an indie rock band from Minneapolis, MN. The band is made up of Abbie (vocals, synth), Tim (guitar, vocals), Micah (bass, vocals), and Jonny (drums). They started as a cover band before deciding to start writing together. They are redefining nostalgia with their covers of 80s, 90s, and 00s songs. They are also working on an EP that will be released later this year. At Porchfest, they will have a Mini Party!! Join Micah and Abbie as they sit on a porch and play acoustic covers and original songs!

Poorwill is a Minneapolis-based indie rock band. Their debut EP Tough Kid featured songs about growing up and moving on, and their new EP - packed with a little bit of yeehaw and a whole lotta heart - will release summer 2024.

An old hound dog, and a can of worms? Hiding from the girls next door? Maybe that old car seat made for two and getting rowdy all night?  Rusty Playground invites you to kick back with us... and Welcome to, Our Rusty Playground.

Spanning generations and genres, Rusty Playground is a five piece strings and harmonies acoustic band from Minneapolis MN. A little blues, a little bluegrass and a whole lot of Americana. We enjoy putting our own twist on things popular and writing new music that reflects on who we are Individually. We may get rowdy, but that’s alright. We’re sure there’s something to make everyone smile, tap their toes and sing along.

An innovative storyteller, artist, husband, father, and executive. Seyi has established himself nationally as an energetic, inspiring, and impactful act. He is Someone to see, hailing as a Nigerian-born citizen of the United States. Seyi is naturally a cultural explorer.  He attributes his faith in Yahweh as a source, foundation, and driving force to his music. His name Oluwaseyi means ‘Yahweh has done it. 

An active-driven musical activist with sounds of Afro Beats, Hip Hop, Reggae, and Pop;  but not respectfully bound or limited to them as genres. His lyrics vibrate the positive energy of the great liberators of our time. “Our ability to heal is rooted in access to our own stories,” says Oyinloye. He uses his skills, tools, and platforms as a storyteller to empower and encourage empathy, and Justice.
Beats to study/chill/rage to
One-man folk noir act from the great north! Playing all your favorite hits from the 20s, 30s, 40s, 50s, 60s, 70s, 80s, 90s, and today!

With heartfelt, literary lyrics, and captivating melodies delivered in a soaring tenor range, *Splash!* brings you musical reflections inspired by philosophy, mysticism, and spiritual practice. His unique warmth provides a balm for your weary soul.

Hailing from the heart of the Twin Cities. Our trio, a delightful blend of folk, rock, bluegrass, and gypsy jazz, showcases captivating three-part harmonies accompanied by the resonant stand-up bass, the melodious fiddle, and the soulful guitar. Our repertoire, a mix of handpicked covers and heartfelt originals, promises to not only get your audience on their feet but also evoke emotions ranging from joy to nostalgia.
ECLECTIC POST-ROCK 3 PIECE HAILING FROM THE FROZEN NORTH
If you come to a Denim Boys show and don't have fun, you can either sue us or come to our house, take your shirt off, and fight us.
The Hazy Phase formed in the Minneapolis area in the spring of 2020. The band is a unique sound that is part garage rock with a healthy dose of old school blues.
The Real Chuck NORAD is a Minneapolis based musical group providing a soundtrack to a dystopian future we deserve.

porch_address: 2601 Hennepin Ave S - Sencha Tea Bar
bio: Rock, roll, and remember: the Recent Future began as five friends playing covers in their basement. Since then, the group has grown to become five friends playing covers in OTHER people’s basements, and making appearances at prestigious events such as their guitarist’s sister’s wedding reception, and now… somebody’s porch in Uptown Minneapolis! The band has been described as "surprisingly talented," and "a lot better than I would have thought." Outside of its varied covers, the Recent Future’s original urban-folk compositions examine life, love, and whether it’s appropriate to switch to half time in every chorus. Lifelong musicians and eternal friends, the Recent Future lives to perform and is dying to see you in the crowd!

Combining the country rock sensibilities of Minneapolis's Chief Opossum with the pounding thunder of Madison-based metal outfit Voltsea, The Unscrupulous Ham Gang unleashes the party animal in all of us. UHG is comprised of three high school friends reuniting for the first time on stage since 2017.

Rooted in the Twin Cities, brothers Jay and Joseph Walker proudly express their Colombian/American heritage through original compositions which feature lyrics in English, Spanish, and Portuguese. Their performances feature expressive interpretations of timeless classics, showcasing an eclectic repertoire and wide range of musical abilities.

Whether performing as a duo, trio, quartet, or more, Joseph and Jay, along with their talented friends, bring joy and a depth of experience, passion, and specialization to every occasion.

Patrick's music has meandered around Jazz-standard styling, folk, acoustic rock and funk, but through it all, he's always considered it Porch Music which is why he's so excited to let it roam in its natural environment. Joined by Miles Porter on upright and electric bass, the duo hopes to tickle your eardrums, give your soul a hug, high-five your heart, and get your head a-bopping, feet a-tapping, and who knows? If you bring the energy, perhaps we'll have a sing along.

Based in St. Paul, MN, The Weeping Covenant is headed by vocalist and songwriter, Michael Beatrez. Writing from a lyrically driven perspective, he generally touches on themes of hope, vulnerability, and love. Beatrez leans into his comfortable sweet spot by singing over soft fingerstyle guitar ballads and rock songs that drive with measured intensity.

The music of The Weeping Covenant is rooted in Americana, with pop sensibilities akin to Jeremy Messersmith, piercing storytelling of Jason Isbell, and spacious, sustained vocals that melt into reverb like the ballads of John Denver. 

A new single is set for release September 2024.
Timothy Sexton has performed his progressive rock keyboard music at First Avenue, the 7th Street entry, and multiple other local venues.
Local hip hop artist tackling a wide variety of styles subjects and themes through his rhymes. Bringing an old school flavor with a modern twist!

Unattractive Giant Monster mutated and grew from the depths of the Twin Cities in Minnesota. Absorbing all kinds of punk rock from Devo to Diarrhea Planet and bonding over the cosmic comedic gumbo of Tim Robinson, these 5 dudes formed to create an unstoppable musical monster! Their debut EP, Return of the Attack of the Mutant Pizza was released in 2023 to critical and commercial success with reviews such as "Neat!", and "Music!".

band_name: Vinny Franco and the Love Channel
bio: We're an R&B/Neosoul band from Minneapolis, we specialize in big band R&B and jazzy neosoul. Loaded up with a horn section, backup vocals, and a full rhythm section, we create a big, energetic, and smooth sound.

Zach is an acoustic based, pop-folk and soul inspired singer songwriter. He has been playing small venues in the Twin Cities since 2008, most notably and enjoyably 7th Street Entry, Aster Cafe, and the 318 Cafe. He was featured in CityPages for his 2019 "Red 19" EP release and spent the following years with a residency at Troubadour Wine Bar on Hennepin.

A singer-songwriter most comfortable with nothing to hide behind but a guitar, Zophia Dadlez has been writing and performing music solo since her high school years. Drawing from contemporary folk, emo, and indie rock influences, her songwriting is poignant and deeply personal. As a multi-instrumentalist and classically trained vocalist, she adorns her recordings with layers of viola, violin and vocal harmony, but creates songs above all to share words and melodies, to get the noise out of her head and to sing out for anyone willing to listen.
Join Sing Play Learn with MacPhail® for a fun-filled afternoon of music! Enjoy a family-friendly concert, make a musical craft, and explore instruments! Free and open to all!
Big rigs, little white pills, dangerous curves and busloads of kids-- what could possibly go wrong?

genre_1: Indie rock, punk, acoustic jam, covers,
genre: Indie rock, punk, acoustic jam, covers,
bio: Footnote and the Divine, a brand new band to the cities featuring Alec as lead singer, Richard on lead guitar and Kayla on drums. Looking to wet their feet playing covers for the neighborhood before heading into the lab to write our own music.

New Seven is the musical project of singer-songwriter Dominic Acito. 
Born in St. Paul, Minnesota, Dominic's family moved around the world, where  to Belgium, Thailand, Japan, Italy, and Scotland. After moving back to Minnesota in 2021, Dominic started New Seven, which gets its name from the local short-hand for the new 7/11 built near where he grew up in Bangkok. 

Music was Dominic's constant companion and obsession during his extensive travels. He describes his style of lyricism as "world-weary and a little literary." His music is stylistically Americana and is often compared to Bill Callahan, Craig Finn, and The National.

In 2021, New Seven released their debut album, The Colossus of Uptown, which gets its name from the near-mythical statue The Colossus of Rhodes. Ian Farmer of Slaughter Beach, Dog, and Modern Baseball said of the album, "Lyrically, musically, and tonally, it's exceptional from track to track."

These days, Dominic performs under New Seven mainly as a solo act, occasionally collaborating with other musicians and adding lesser-known cover songs discovered during his travels to his ever-growing setlist of original songs.

Paper Chain is a trio from Minneapolis, MN lead by composer and lyricist Caitlin Benson. The group features Caitlin on lead vocals and cello, Andrew S. Lentz on piano, Chris Cuellar on guitar, and makes prominent use of three-part vocal harmony arranged by the group’s pianist. Paper Chain’s music is the effortless synthesis of modern chamber-pop with 19th century romantic composers such as Beethoven, Schumann, and Grieg. Caitlin’s writing straddles the feelings of open prairie skies and hurried metropolitan energy.  Their first album is currently in production and will launch with the debut of their first single “Eusebius” in summer of 2024.

Who the hell is/are Penny and the Bandits? Well.. for a pandemic, it’s been Jen Scott. I made up a band in my head during the pandemic so I'd have a vehicle for the songs I was writing. Cuz how else do you start a band during a pandemic? I've lucky enough to be joined by James Rone, Samantha Baker-Harris, Will Roberts, Josh Kaplan, Matt Patric, and am hoping to keep them for as long as they let me. <3

band_name: Scott Hefte and the Bury ‘em Deep
bio: From the ashes of such bands as Seymore Saves the World, Superdanger, Me and My Arrow, and Beasthead, rises a dark and brooding indie-western soundtrack for your apocalypse. Scott Hefte and the Bury ‘em Deep have combined to create hellish landscapes of a dystopian nightmare while not forgetting the righteous influences of old school country, indie-pop, and noise rock. The resulting sound is one of Johnny Cash, Phil Collins, and Godspeed You Black Emperor, fighting a bloodless three way cage match for superiority. No one wins but you, when you dig the music of Scott Hefte and the Bury ‘em Deep.
We're an Alt-Rock band from the Twin Cities ready to bring you the latest sounds from The Violet Press!

Couch Potato Massacre is a pop punk band from Minneapolis, MN that writes songs about movies, television shows, and video games. If you're into groups like Chixdiggit, The Copyrights, Groovie Ghoulies, House Boat, or The Ramones... You will probably enjoy Couch Potato Massacre.
King Sized Coffin is a Minneapolis band with a lot of members, a lot of instruments, and a lot of spooky songs. For Fans of Tom Waits, Nick Cave, Harley Poe, The Cure, and The Misfits.
We are 3 Native American locals who have come together to make awesome all original rock music. Come party with us.
Sam just thinks we're a Weezer ripoff. Tom thinks Brad should get over his ex. Brad just wants to dance. Instead it's 3am and we're still staring at the ceiling fan.
